      <h2>Safety</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        Read all safety warnings, instructions, illustrations and specifications provided with this tool. Failure to follow them may result in electric shock, fire, and/or serious injury.
      </div>

      <h3>Nailer-Specific Warnings</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Always assume the tool contains fasteners.</strong> Careless handling can fire a pin unexpectedly.</li>
        <li><strong>Never point the tool at yourself or anyone nearby.</strong> Unexpected triggering will discharge a pin.</li>
        <li><strong>Do not actuate the tool unless it is placed firmly against the workpiece.</strong> Off the workpiece, the pin may deflect.</li>
        <li><strong>Remove the battery pack before clearing a jam</strong> or making any adjustment &mdash; the mechanism can be under compression and discharge a pin forcefully.</li>
        <li>Do not drive pins near the edge of material; the workpiece can split and the pin can ricochet or follow the grain (a "shiner") and exit the side.</li>
        <li>Do not drive pins onto the heads of other fasteners or with the tool at a steep angle &mdash; recoil, jams, or ricochet can injure you.</li>
        <li>Never grasp the tool by the magazine while in use; a mis&#8209;driven pin can exit the nose.</li>
        <li>Do not use the tool for fastening electrical cables, and do not use it in the presence of flammable dust, gas, or fumes.</li>
        <li>Do not discharge into open air, concrete, stone, extremely hard woods, or knots. Never use the body or top cap as a hammer.</li>
        <li>Disconnect the battery and empty the magazine before leaving the work area, passing the tool to another operator, or moving via ladders or scaffolding.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Personal Protection</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>ANSI Z87.1 (CAN/CSA Z94.3) eye protection &mdash; everyday eyeglasses are not safety glasses.</li>
        <li>ANSI S12.6 (S3.19) hearing protection.</li>
        <li>NIOSH/OSHA/MSHA respiratory protection where dust is present.</li>
      </ul>

